      <description>&lt;p&gt;The best resources on your journey of developing R packages are, of course, the two editions of R Packages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://r-pkgs.had.co.nz/&#34;&gt;R Packages, ed 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://r-pkgs.org/&#34;&gt;R Packages, ed 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re submitting to CRAN, you&#39;ll also want to keep a few extra resources handy:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://colinfay.me/writing-r-extensions&#34;&gt;Writing R Extensions&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ThinkR-open/prepare-for-cran&#34;&gt;Preparing your package for a CRAN submission Checklist&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For generally improving your code writing and debugging skills, we recommend:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://adv-r.hadley.nz/&#34;&gt;Advanced R, ed. 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://rstats.wtf/&#34;&gt;What They Forgot to Teach You About R&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/jennybc/code-smells-and-feels&#34;&gt;Code Smells and Feels&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://style.tidyverse.org/&#34;&gt;The Tidyverse Styleguide&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
